n\\nI'm exploring whether we can avoid a full Session.connect by using the public API. A session needs to be connected, but using `openChannel` might not work if it's not connected. There've been native failures due to missing JSch algorithms. Should I reference implementation classes in the test? It seems like adding `keepSessionImplementationsReachable()` might be necessary.\\n\\nHowever, I encountered a native NPE at line 70 caused by `Class.forName(getConfig(\\\"diffie-hellman-group1-sha1\\\"))`. I wonder if importing new DHG1(), DH, SHA1, MD5, SignatureRSA, TripleDESCBC, and HMACSHA1 would help. It looks like reflection might still fail unless properly configured.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Native Session Failures**\\n\\nI'm pondering the existing SessionTest, which calls `keepSessionImplementationsReachable`. It seems there might be a native failure due to metadata being absent, which makes the method unreachable since it runs before the connect at line 63. I'm curious why it wasn't included. The native image typically includes code from methods, but maybe simply creating a new DHG1() isn't sufficient to ensure everything is set up correctly. I need to figure out why this isn't resolving the issue.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MUi3zzssWpd8kHuj5iYKnoGM|fc_011dce07c6b0df9c016a110f49579c81939cd36f01280bf2be", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/ChannelForwardedTCPIPTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public class ChannelForwardedTCPIPTest {\n    private static final String USER = \"forwarded-tcpip-coverage\";", "newText": "public class ChannelForwardedTCPIPTest implements ForwardedTCPIPDaemon {\n    private static final AtomicReference<ChannelForwardedTCPIP> CHANNEL = new AtomicReference<>();\n    private static final AtomicReference<Object[]> ARGUMENTS = new AtomicReference<>();\n    private static CountDownLatch invocationLatch = new CountDownLatch(1);\n\n